%% Diagram: Lock implementation decision tree
%% Type: flowchart
%%{init: {'htmlLabels': false}}%%
flowchart TD
    A[Need a distributed lock] --> B{Correctness critical?}
    B -->|"No: efficiency only"| C{Fault tolerance needed?}
    B -->|"Yes: data corruption risk"| D{Resource can validate fencing token?}
    C -->|"No"| E["Redis single-node (SET NX PX)"]
    C -->|"Yes"| F["Redlock — 5 nodes"]
    D -->|"No"| X["Stop — fencing-capable resource is required;<br/>otherwise no lock is correct"]
    D -->|"Yes"| Y{Existing infra?}
    Y -->|"ZooKeeper / Kafka stack"| G["ZooKeeper + zxid fencing"]
    Y -->|"Kubernetes / etcd"| H["etcd + revision fencing"]
    Y -->|"Consul (service mesh)"| I["Consul session + LockIndex fencing"]
    Y -->|"Postgres only, single DB"| J["pg_advisory_xact_lock + version column"]
    Y -->|"Greenfield"| G
